Module compiler

module compiler
The compiler for the Prev25 programming language. The compiler should be run as

$ java compiler.Compiler command-line-options...

The following command line options are available:
  • --src-file-name=file-name: The name of the source file, i.e., the file containing the code to be compiled.
  • --dst-file-name=file-name: The name of the destination file, i.e., the file containing the compiled code.
  • --target-phase=phase-name: The name of the last phase to be performed, or none or all (default).
  • --logged-phase=phase-name: The name of the phase the report file is to be generated for, or none or all (default).
  • --xml=prefix: The prefix of the name of the generated xml report files (unless specified the base name of the source file name is used).
  • --xsl=dir-name: The directory where xsl templates used by generated xml report files are stored.
  • --dev-mode=on|off: Development mode (browse the source code for information).
The source file can be specified by its name only, i.e., without --src-file-name. If the source file is not specified, the last modified .prev25 file found in the working directory is used. Unless the name of the destination file is specified, the base name of the source file name is used.
